<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="1986_Mets_reunion">1986 Mets reunion</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Ray_Knight&amp;action=edit&amp;section=10" title="Edit section: 1986 Mets reunion"><span>edit</span></a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h2>
<p>Knight was one of several members of the 1986 championship team not to attend the 20th anniversary celebration at <a href="/wiki/Shea_Stadium" title="Shea Stadium">Shea Stadium</a> on August 19, 2006; the others included manager <a href="/wiki/Davey_Johnson" title="Davey Johnson">Davey Johnson</a>, (who was managing <a href="/wiki/United_States_national_baseball_team" title="United States national baseball team">Team USA</a> in <a href="/wiki/Cuba" title="Cuba">Cuba</a>), <a href="/wiki/Dwight_Gooden" title="Dwight Gooden">Dwight Gooden</a> (who was serving a jail sentence), <a href="/wiki/Roger_McDowell" title="Roger McDowell">Roger McDowell</a> (who was the <a href="/wiki/Atlanta_Braves" title="Atlanta Braves">Atlanta Braves</a> pitching coach at the time), <a href="/wiki/Lee_Mazzilli" title="Lee Mazzilli">Lee Mazzilli</a> (who was the <a href="/wiki/New_York_Yankees" title="New York Yankees">New York Yankees</a> bench coach at the time), and pitching coach <a href="/wiki/Mel_Stottlemyre" title="Mel Stottlemyre">Mel Stottlemyre</a>. Knight's absence was due to a previous commitment.<sup id="cite_ref-14" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-14">&#91;14&#93;</a></sup>
</p>
<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Personal_life">Personal life</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Ray_Knight&amp;action=edit&amp;section=11" title="Edit section: Personal life"><span>edit</span></a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h2>
<p>Knight married <a href="/wiki/LPGA" title="LPGA">LPGA</a> <a href="/wiki/Golf" title="Golf">golfer</a> <a href="/wiki/Nancy_Lopez" title="Nancy Lopez">Nancy Lopez</a> on October 25, 1982, in <a href="/wiki/Pelham,_Georgia" title="Pelham, Georgia">Pelham, Georgia</a>. The wedding, the second for both, was at the home of his partner in a Pelham sporting goods store.<sup id="cite_ref-:0_1-1" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-:0-1">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> Knight and Lopez met by chance in <a href="/wiki/Korakuen_Stadium" title="Korakuen Stadium">Korakuen Stadium</a> in <a href="/wiki/Tokyo" title="Tokyo">Tokyo</a> in 1978.<sup id="cite_ref-:1_15-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-:1-15">&#91;15&#93;</a></sup> He and Lopez had three daughters together, Ashley Marie (1983), Erinn Shea (1986) and Torri Heather Knight (1991).<sup id="cite_ref-16" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-16">&#91;16&#93;</a></sup> They lived in <a href="/wiki/Albany,_Georgia" title="Albany, Georgia">Albany</a>, <a href="/wiki/Georgia_(U.S._state)" title="Georgia (U.S. state)">Georgia</a>, and also had a home in <a href="/wiki/The_Villages,_Florida" title="The Villages, Florida">The Villages</a>, <a href="/wiki/Florida" title="Florida">Florida</a>.<sup id="cite_ref-17" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-17">&#91;17&#93;</a></sup> Lopez designed her first golf course for The Villages and the three nines of the 27-hole Lopez Legacy course are named for the daughters: Ashley Meadows, Torri Pines, and Erinn Glenn.<sup id="cite_ref-18" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-18">&#91;18&#93;</a></sup> In 1985, he had a 7 handicap in golf and sometimes caddied for her, but not in big tournaments.<sup id="cite_ref-:1_15-1" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-:1-15">&#91;15&#93;</a></sup> Knight and Lopez divorced in 2009.<sup id="cite_ref-19" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-19">&#91;19&#93;</a></sup> A son from his first marriage, Brooks Knight, died in 2022.<sup id="cite_ref-:1_15-2" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-:1-15">&#91;15&#93;</a></sup> 
</p><p>In 2013, Phoebe Putney Hospital in Albany, Georgia, unveiled a street on the property named Ray Knight Way.<sup id="cite_ref-20" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-20">&#91;20&#93;</a></sup>
</p><p>Knight is good friends with former Reds' teammate <a href="/wiki/Harry_Spilman" title="Harry Spilman">Harry Spilman</a>, who grew up twenty minutes away from Knight in Georgia. While they were both in the Reds' system, the two spent $700 on a <a href="/wiki/Pitching_machine" title="Pitching machine">pitching machine</a> to work on their hitting.<sup id="cite_ref-replace_rose_21-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-replace_rose-21">&#91;21&#93;</a></sup>
</p><p>Knight is a member of the <a href="/wiki/Golden_Gloves" title="Golden Gloves">Golden Gloves</a> boxing association.
</p><p>On October 23, 2017, Knight was arrested after an altercation at his condo in the <a href="/wiki/Alexandria,_Virginia" title="Alexandria, Virginia">Alexandria</a>, <a href="/wiki/Virginia" title="Virginia">Virginia</a>, area with an unidentified 33-year-old man. Both were taken to the hospital and Knight was charged with <a href="/wiki/Assault" title="Assault">assault</a> and <a href="/wiki/Battery_(crime)" title="Battery (crime)">battery</a>.<sup id="cite_ref-22" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-22">&#91;22&#93;</a></sup> The charges were subsequently dropped.<sup id="cite_ref-23" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-23">&#91;23&#93;</a></sup>
</p><p>Knight participated in the 2021 <a href="/wiki/ESPN" title="ESPN">ESPN</a> <i><a href="/wiki/30_for_30" title="30 for 30">30 for 30</a></i> documentary series about the <a href="/wiki/1986_New_York_Mets_season" title="1986 New York Mets season">1986 New York Mets</a> season, <i>Once Upon a Time in Queens.</i><sup id="cite_ref-24" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-24">&#91;24&#93;</a></sup>
</p>
